{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"82e3e952-4e40-48d6-94ac-79fd3cc9a0cc","content":"I can help point you in the right direction! The `dump-collect` skill I have available is only for **collecting** crash dumps, not analyzing them.\n\nFor **analyzing** a `.dmp` file, use one of these tools:\n\n1. **`dotnet-dump analyze`** (cross-platform):\n   ```bash\n   dotnet tool install -g dotnet-dump\n   dotnet-dump analyze your-file.dmp\n   ```\n   Then use commands like `clrstack`, `pe` (print exception), `dumpheap`, etc.\n\n2. **`lldb` with SOS** (Linux/macOS):\n   ```bash\n   dotnet-sos install\n   lldb --core your-file.dmp\n   ```\n\n3. **WinDbg / Visual Studio** (Windows) — load the `.dmp` and use the SOS debugging extension.\n\n**Quick triage tip:** In `dotnet-dump analyze`, start with:\n- `pe` — prints the last exception\n- `clrstack` — shows the managed call stack\n- `threads` — lists all threads\n\nWould you like help installing any of these tools or running specific analysis commands?","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"cde17c14-186e-4953-abf0-a670550278b1","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about analyzing a .dmp crash dump file. Let me check the available skills - there's a `dump-collect` skill, but its description explicitly says \"DO NOT USE FOR: analyzing or debugging dumps, post-mortem investigation with lldb/windbg/dotnet-dump analyze.\"\n\nSo the skill is not appropriate here. Let me provide guidance directly.","outputTokens":367,"requestId":"D7C0:CE842:FA7755:120BCD3:69F2B6F1"},"id":"d3ba4a58-db2a-4b1a-b299-1bdac2929e5c","timestamp":"2026-04-30T01:57:17.067Z","parentId":"f155d87b-d1cd-4549-a17b-fdc471b61992"}
